request.description:
### Get Quotes

This endpoint makes an HTTP GET request to retrieve quotes for a specific date and time, parking preferences, vehicle length, and lot.

#### Request Parameters

- `doDate`: 2024-05-13 12:00 PM
- `puDate`: 2024-05-26 12:00 PM
- `pref`: VALET
- `vehicleLength`: STANDARD
- `lot`: LOT_2
    

#### Response

The response will include a status and data object with various quote details, such as city tax, port fee, currency, lot type, extra fee, and different rates for online, non-online, anonymous, and reference bookings.

request.description:
This API endpoint allows the creation of a reservation for a member. The request should be sent as an HTTP POST to the URL [http://localhost/member/reservation](http://localhost/member/reservation). The request body should be in x-www-form-urlencoded format and include parameters for various reservation details such as doDate, puDate, pref, vehicleLength, lot, vehicleId, makeModel, licensePlate, driverId, email, fullName, phone, stripeToken, cardId, paymentDetails, paxCount, coupon, returnFlight, pricing, and isRegular.

The response of this request can be documented as a JSON schema to define the structure of the response data.

request.description:
### POST /v1/api/v1.0/member/reservation/{reservation_id}/cancel

This endpoint is used to cancel a specific reservation for a member.

#### Request Body

- `dropOffDate` (string, optional): The date for the drop off.
- `driverEmail` (string, optional): The email of the driver.
    

#### Response

Upon successful cancellation, the response will include:

- `status` (boolean): Indicates the status of the cancellation request.
- `data` (object): Contains detailed information about the cancelled reservation, including the vehicle, driver, pricing, wallet transactions, and owner details.
- `redirect_url` (string): The URL to redirect the user after the cancellation.
    

In case of an error, an appropriate error message will be returned.

request.description:
### Cancel Guest Reservation

This endpoint allows the cancellation of a guest reservation.

#### Request Body
- `dropOffDate` (string, optional): The drop-off date for the reservation.
- `driverEmail` (string, optional): The email of the driver associated with the reservation.

#### Response
The response will be a JSON object with the following properties:
- `status` (boolean): Indicates the status of the cancellation request.
- `data` (object): Contains details about the cancelled reservation, including reservation ID, drop-off and pick-up times, driver and vehicle information, pricing details, etc.
  - `id` (number): The ID of the reservation.
  - `actualDropOffTime` (string, nullable): The actual drop-off time.
  - `actualPickUpTime` (string, nullable): The actual pick-up time.
  - `claimId` (string, nullable): The claim ID.
  - `confirmationCode` (string): The confirmation code of the reservation.
  - `createdDate` (string): The date of creation of the reservation.
  - `dropOffTime` (string): The drop-off time.
  - `isDeleted` (number): Indicates if the reservation is deleted.
  - `lastModifiedDate` (string): The date of the last modification.
  - `lotType` (string): The type of parking lot.
  - `paidTillTime` (string): The time till which the reservation is paid.
  - `parkingPreference` (string): The parking preference.
  - `paxCount` (number): The count of passengers.
  - `pickUpTime` (string): The pick-up time.
  - `returnAirline` (string): The return airline.
  - `returnFlightNo` (string): The return flight number.
  - `status` (string): The status of the reservation.
  - `version` (number): The version of the reservation.
  - `createdBy_id` (number, nullable): The ID of the creator of the reservation.
  - `lastModifiedBy_id` (number, nullable): The ID of the last modifier of the reservation.
  - `driver_id` (number): The ID of the driver associated with the reservation.
  - `vehicle_id` (number): The ID of the vehicle associated with the reservation.
  - `vehicle` (object): Details of the vehicle associated with the reservation.
    - `id` (number): The ID of the vehicle.
    - `isDeleted` (number): Indicates if the vehicle is deleted.
    - `version` (number): The version of the vehicle.
    - `createdDate` (string): The date of creation of the vehicle.
    - `lastModifiedDate` (string): The date of the last modification of the vehicle.
    - `makeModel` (string): The make and model of the vehicle.
    - `nickName` (string, nullable): The nickname of the vehicle.
    - `plate` (string): The plate number of the vehicle.
    - `preferred` (string, nullable): Indicates if the vehicle is preferred.
    - `vehicleLength` (string): The length of the vehicle.
    - `createdBy_id` (number, nullable): The ID of the creator of the vehicle.
    - `lastModifiedBy_id` (number, nullable): The ID of the last modifier of the vehicle.
  - `driver` (object): Details of the driver associated with the reservation.
    - `id` (number): The ID of the driver.
    - `isDeleted` (number): Indicates if the driver is deleted.
    - `version` (number): The version of the driver.
    - `createdDate` (string): The date of creation of the driver.
    - `lastModifiedDate` (string): The date of the last modification of the driver.
    - `email` (string): The email of the driver.
    - `full_name` (string): The full name of the driver.
    - `phone` (string): The phone number of the driver.
    - `preferred` (string, nullable): Indicates if the driver is preferred.
    - `createdBy_id` (number, nullable): The ID of the creator of the driver.
    - `lastModifiedBy_id` (number, nullable): The ID of the last modifier of the driver.
  - `pricing` (array): Details of the pricing for the reservation.
    - `id` (number): The ID of the pricing.
    - `isDeleted` (number): Indicates if the pricing is deleted.
    - `version` (number): The version of the pricing.
    - `createdDate` (string): The date of creation of the pricing.
    - `lastModifiedDate` (string): The date of the last modification of the pricing.
    - ... (other pricing details)
  - `redirect_url` (string): The redirect URL.

request.description:
This HTTP POST request is used to sign in a user. The request should include the user's email, password, and client information in the request body. The response will include a success status indicating if the sign-in was successful, a token for authentication, and the user's ID.

### Request Body
- email (string): The user's email.
- password (string): The user's password.
- client (string): The client information.

### Response
- success (boolean): Indicates if the sign-in was successful.
- token (string): Authentication token for the user.
- user_id (integer): The ID of the signed-in user.
